# Delivery and Verification

## Definition of Done

A task is done only when:
- Code changes are applied and coherent with existing architecture.
- Type and test checks for impacted scope pass.
- Risks and trade-offs are stated for non-trivial decisions.

## Verification defaults

- Run TypeScript check (`npx tsc --noEmit`) for code changes.
- Run targeted tests first; run broader test suites when risk is cross-cutting.
- If verification cannot run, explain why and provide exact commands for user execution.

## Change communication

- Report what changed, where, and why.
- Include any follow-up work or residual risks.
- Do not claim success without evidence from executed checks.

## Safety gates

- Ask before destructive or irreversible operations.
- Keep commits and PR scope focused when requested.
